<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="257" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,651,1362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,301,651,678]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Diagnosis.—</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[442,584,652,677]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,584,652,677]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Heterometra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with brachials wedge-shaped, not exceedingly short, and with ends not quite parallel. Enlarged proximal pinnules smooth, with proximal segments keeled. Cirri 
<quantity box="[1089,1211,687,714]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="24.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="23.0">23–25 mm</quantity>
long, of 31–35 seg- ments; longest cirrals about as long as broad or slightly longer than broad; distal cirrals with width to length ratio 1.5–2.0, with aboral tubercles. Arms 
<quantity box="[562,737,759,786]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25705" metricValueMax="2.5125" metricValueMin="0.0016" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="12570.5" valueMax="25125.0" valueMin="16.0">16–25, 125 mm</quantity>
long. P1 and P2 similar, equally long, with 26 segments; much longer and slightly stouter than PD. P3 scarcely longer than PD (A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[939,1075,795,822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref14208" refString="Clark, A. H. (1941) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids. Part 4 a. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 603, pls. 1 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.4 a" type="journal article" year="1941">Clark, 1941</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="257" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,651,1362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,831,858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Material examined.—</emphasis>
None in this study. Specimens were previously collected at Bassas de Pedro by 
<collectionCode box="[1368,1436,832,858]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">RIMS</collectionCode>
<taxonomicName authority="(A. H. Clark, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="A. H. Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[151,509,867,894]" genus="Investigator" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,286,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Investigator</emphasis>
(A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[364,500,867,894]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref14208" refString="Clark, A. H. (1941) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids. Part 4 a. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 603, pls. 1 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.4 a" type="journal article" year="1941">Clark, 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1179,903,930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,651,1362]" box="[199,1179,903,930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,903,930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Distribution.—</emphasis>
Bassas de Pedro, 
<collectingCountry box="[576,734,903,929]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Lakshadweep</collectingCountry>
. No depth recorded (A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[1030,1167,903,930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref14208" refString="Clark, A. H. (1941) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids. Part 4 a. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 603, pls. 1 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.4 a" type="journal article" year="1941">Clark, 1941</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="257" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,651,1362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,940,966]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Remarks.—</emphasis>
This species is currently known only from the nine specimens collected at Bassas de Pedro. It is unclear if 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[265,382,976,1001]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="compta">
<emphasis box="[265,382,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">H. compta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in shallow water (&lt;
<quantity box="[765,825,975,1002]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</quantity>
) or not. 
<bibRefCitation author="NIMA &amp; National Imagery &amp; Mapping Agency" box="[921,1076,976,1002]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="99 - 118" refId="ref16173" refString="NIMA (National Imagery and Mapping Agency) (2002) Sector 5, The Laccadive Islands and the Maldive Islands. Sailing Directions (Enroute): India and the Bay of Bengal, Publication 173, 99 - 118." type="journal article" year="2002">NIMA (2002)</bibRefCitation>
gives the depth range of Bassas de Pedro as 16.4– 
<specimenCount box="[356,405,1011,1038]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" type="generic">
<quantity box="[356,401,1011,1038]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Most records for the genus are &lt;
<quantity box="[784,844,1011,1038]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</quantity>
, but species have been collected to depths of 
<quantity box="[1364,1436,1011,1038]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="125.0">125 m</quantity>
(possibly 
<quantity box="[261,332,1047,1074]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3599999999999999" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" unit="m" value="136.0">136 m</quantity>
) (A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[417,552,1047,1074]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref14208" refString="Clark, A. H. (1941) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids. Part 4 a. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 603, pls. 1 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.4 a" type="journal article" year="1941">Clark, 1941</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Messing, C. G. &amp; Tay, T. S." box="[564,807,1047,1074]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="627 - 658" refId="ref15896" refString="Messing, C. G. &amp; Tay, T. S. (2016) Extant Crinoidea (Echinodermata) of Singapore. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement No. 34, 627 - 658." type="book chapter" year="2016">Messing &amp; Tay, 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and RIMS 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. H. Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[948,1083,1048,1073]" genus="Investigator" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[948,1083,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Investigator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also trawled and dredged in far deeper water (e.g., A.M. Clark &amp; A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H. &amp; Clark, A. M." box="[595,732,1083,1110]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref14390" refString="Clark, A. H. &amp; Clark, A. M. (1967) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids, part 5. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 860. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.3" type="journal article" year="1967">Clark, 1967</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[753,985,1084,1109]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="compta">
<emphasis box="[753,985,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Heterometra compta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of several species recorded from the western Indian Ocean and Red Sea that differ morphologically only in minor characters, many of which likely vary with growth and environmental conditions (e.g., arm number and length; cirrus length, and number and proportion of segments; aboral cirrus ornamentation, and relative lengths and numbers of segments of oral pinnules, and proportions of pinnule segments) (A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[607,744,1227,1254]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref14208" refString="Clark, A. H. (1941) A monograph of the existing crinoids. Vol. 1. The Comatulids. Part 4 a. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 82, 1 - 603, pls. 1 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.82.4 a" type="journal article" year="1941">Clark, 1941</bibRefCitation>
; A.M. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M." box="[824,960,1227,1254]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="75 - 156" refId="ref14449" refString="Clark, A. M. (1972) Some crinoids from the Indian Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology, 24, 75 - 156." type="journal article" year="1972">Clark, 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, J. I. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[974,1253,1227,1254]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="379 - 413" refId="ref15368" refString="Marshall, J. I. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1981) The crinoids of Madagascar. Bulletin du Museium national d'histoire naturelle, Paris, 4 e Serie, 3, Section A, No. 2, 379 - 413. [http: // bionames. org / bionames-archive / issn / 0181 - 0626 / 3 / 379. pdf]" type="book chapter" year="1981">Marshall &amp; Rowe, 1981</bibRefCitation>
). Three of these (
<taxonomicName authority="A. H. Clark, 1911 c" authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[161,501,1263,1290]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="gravieri">
<emphasis box="[161,285,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">H. gravieri</emphasis>
A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[355,501,1263,1290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref13741" refString="Clark, A. H. (1911 c) The Recent crinoids of the coasts of Africa. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 40 (1808), 1 - 51. [https: // repository. si. edu / bitstream / handle / 10088 / 14309 / 1 / USNMP- 40 _ 1808 _ 1911. pdf] https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.40 - 1808.1" type="journal article" year="1911">Clark, 1911c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="A. H. Clark, 1911 c" authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1911" box="[561,890,1263,1290]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="joubini">
<emphasis box="[561,674,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">H. joubini</emphasis>
A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[744,890,1263,1290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref13741" refString="Clark, A. H. (1911 c) The Recent crinoids of the coasts of Africa. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 40 (1808), 1 - 51. [https: // repository. si. edu / bitstream / handle / 10088 / 14309 / 1 / USNMP- 40 _ 1808 _ 1911. pdf] https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.40 - 1808.1" type="journal article" year="1911">Clark, 1911c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1065,1263,1289]" name="Tanzania" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(A. H. Clark, 1911 c)" baseAuthorityName="A. H. Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[1125,1436,1263,1290]" class="Crinoidea" family="Himerometridae" genus="Heterometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis box="[1125,1204,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="257">H. ater</emphasis>
(A.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. H." box="[1283,1428,1263,1290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref13741" refString="Clark, A. H. (1911 c) The Recent crinoids of the coasts of Africa. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 40 (1808), 1 - 51. [https: // repository. si. edu / bitstream / handle / 10088 / 14309 / 1 / USNMP- 40 _ 1808 _ 1911. pdf] https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.40 - 1808.1" type="journal article" year="1911">Clark, 1911c</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Red Sea) remain known from one specimen each. All of these species require additional research to verify their status.
</paragraph>
